                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4a/162</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation with M.
                        Viviani, of the French Delegation, December 9, 1921, 6:15 p.m.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1921-12-09T18:15:00-05:00"
                        >December 9, 1921, 6:15 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="participants">
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Present</hi>: <list>
                            <item>M. Viviani</item>
                            <item>M. Camerlynck</item>
                            <item>Mr. Hughes</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Mr. Viviani called to read a message which he had just received from M. Briand
                    authorizing him to express the assent of France to the quadruple treaty.
                    Arrangements were then made for the plenary session the next morning.</p>
            </div>
